# Cursor Rules for Lukman's Portfolio Website

## Project Patterns

### Styling Patterns
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling instead of custom CSS
- Follow mobile-first approach with sm:, md:, lg: breakpoints
- Use the Geist font family (Sans and Mono variants) for typography
- Primary background color: #f8f4ec (light beige)
- Highlight color: #ff914d (orange)

### Component Patterns
- Reuse existing UI components from src/components/ui when possible
- New animations should follow existing patterns using Framer Motion or GSAP
- Interactive elements should include hover states and smooth transitions
- 3D elements use React Three Fiber and follow existing scene/model patterns

### File Structure
- Page components in src/pages directory
- Reusable components in src/components
- UI components in src/components/ui
- Project components in src/components/projects
- Utility functions in src/utils
- Custom hooks in src/hooks

### Naming Conventions
- React components use PascalCase (e.g., Hero.tsx)
- Utility functions use camelCase (e.g., generateSlug.ts)
- Files use lowercase with hyphens for multi-word names (e.g., custom-button.tsx)

### Animation Techniques
- Use Lenis for smooth scrolling
- Use Framer Motion for UI animations
- Use GSAP for complex animation sequences
- Use React Three Fiber for 3D animations
- Text animations use custom components like Typewriter and TextLoop

## Development Preferences
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow a component-based architecture
- Maintain responsive design for all screen sizes
- Optimize images and animations for performance
- Keep dependencies minimal and up-to-date 